  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of butter over medium heat.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Pour in the heavy cream and bring to a simmer.",
    "Stir in the shredded mozzarella cheese and grated onion, until melted and smooth.",
    "Add the shredded smoked cheddar cheese and stir until well combined.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Pour the egg mixture over the cheese mixture in the skillet.",
    "Cook for 2-3 minutes, until the edges start to set.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 15-20 minutes, until the frittata is set.",
    "Remove from the oven and let it cool for 5 minutes, before slicing and serving.",
    "Garnish with chopped spring onions, if desired.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!"
  ],
